[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0;34mGenerated Configuration Summary:\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;34m===============================\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Database Name: \u001b[0;32mopendocman\u001b[0m\r\nDatabase User: \u001b[0;32mKhaiFatma\u001b[0m\r\nDatabase Password: \u001b[0;32m[Generated - 24 chars]\u001b[0m\r\nRoot Password: \u001b[0;32m[Generated - 32 chars]\u001b[0m\r\nAdmin Password: \u001b[0;32m[Generated/Custom - 8 chars]\u001b[0m\r\nSession Secret: \u001b[0;32m[Generated - 64 chars]\u001b[0m\r\nHostname: \u001b[0;32modm.local\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "HTTP Port: \u001b[0;32m8080\u001b[0m\r\nHTTPS Port: \u001b[0;32m443\u001b[0m\r\nDatabase Port: \u001b[0;32m3306\u001b[0m\r\nEmail: \u001b[0;32madmin@odm.local\u001b[0m\r\nTimezone: \u001b[0;32mJakarta\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;33mImportant Notes:\u001b[0m\r\n• Your .env file contains sensitive information - do not commit it to version control\r\n• Make sure to add .env to your .gitignore file\r\n• Keep a secure backup of your .env file\r\n• The admin username will be 'admin' with the generated/custom password\r\n\r\n\u001b[0;34mNext Steps:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "1. Review and customize additional settings in .env if needed\r\n2. Run: \u001b[0;32mdocker-compose up -d --build\u001b[0m\r\n3. Access your application at: \u001b[0;32mhttp://localhost:8080\u001b[0m\r\n4. Login with username: \u001b[0;32madmin\u001b[0m and your generated password\r\n\r\n\u001b[0;32mSetup complete! 🚀\u001b[0m\r\n"]
